`libzstd` appears to be available in [most distros](https://pkgs.org/download/libzstd) (though Ubuntu's is a bit old) so add the option to build against it. I could not find any evidence that this code is patched, so it should be clean to do so. I'm not sure about the server change as it doesn't build on `master` for me.

I'm not sure if a version check is necessary; it doesn't look like many places use one, but I can try to add one if needed.

@akien-mga this is in reference to my comment on #8983.
